.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.GETTIMEZONETRANSITION" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.getTimeZoneTransition \-
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.getTimeZoneTransition()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]getTimeZoneTransition()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object representing the closest
instant after or before this instant at which the time zone\(cqs UTC
offset changes (the returned instant is the first instant after the
change), or \f[CR]null\f[R] if there is no such transition.
This is useful for finding out the offset rules of a time zone, such as
its daylight saving time pattern.
.PP
Note that instants returned about the future may be unreliable, for
example due to changes to the time zone definitions.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getTimeZoneTransition(direction)
getTimeZoneTransition(options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]direction\f[R]
A string representing the \f[CR]direction\f[R] option.
This is a convenience overload, so
\f[CR]getTimeZoneTransition(direction)\f[R] is equivalent to
\f[CR]getTimeZoneTransition({ direction })\f[R], where
\f[CR]direction\f[R] is a string.
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R]
An object containing the following property:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]direction\f[R]
Whether to search before or after the current instant.
Must be one of \f[CR]\(dqnext\(dq\f[R] or \f[CR]\(dqprevious\(dq\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object with instant \f[CR]t\f[R],
such that:
.IP \(bu 2
The time zone offset at \f[CR]t\f[R] is different from the offset one
nanosecond before \f[CR]t\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]t < this.epochNanoseconds\f[R] if \f[CR]direction\f[R] is
\f[CR]\(dqprevious\(dq\f[R], or \f[CR]t > this.epochNanoseconds\f[R] if
\f[CR]direction\f[R] is \f[CR]\(dqnext\(dq\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
For all instants between \f[CR]this.epochNanoseconds\f[R] and
\f[CR]t\f[R], exclusive, the offset is constant.
.PP
If there is no such transition, \f[CR]null\f[R] is returned.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Finding the next time zone transition
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2024\-01\-01T00\-05:00[America/New_York]\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] transition = dt.getTimeZoneTransition(\(dqnext\(dq);
console.log(transition.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2024\-03\-10T03:00:00\-04:00[America/New_York]\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] transition2 = transition.getTimeZoneTransition(\(dqnext\(dq);
console.log(transition2.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2024\-11\-03T01:00:00\-05:00[America/New_York]\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] transition3 = dt.getTimeZoneTransition(\(dqprevious\(dq);
console.log(transition3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2023\-11\-05T01:00:00\-05:00[America/New_York]\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] dt2 = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(\(dq2024\-01\-01T00Z[UTC]\(dq);
console.log(dt2.getTimeZoneTransition(\(dqnext\(dq)); \f[I]// null\f[R]
.EE
